Fractal abstract events - the pattern ALREADY EXISTS in compiler.kz!

The real compiler.coordinate.default is a FLOW:
- Pipeline IS the continuation chain
- Each step is a separate event
- Error handling built into flow (| failed f |>)
- compiler.coordinate intentionally unimplemented for user override

What abstract events add:
- Make the override pattern EXPLICIT
- Enable delegation to default from within override
- Compile-time single-implementation enforcement

Current: Users override by implementing compiler.coordinate
Future: ~[abstract] event + cross-module overrides for explicit contract

The fractal structure already exists:
- compiler.coordinate (whole pipeline)
  - compiler.coordinate.frontend
  - compiler.coordinate.transform_taps
  - compiler.coordinate.analysis
  - compiler.coordinate.test_generation
  - compiler.coordinate.optimize
  - compiler.coordinate.emission

Each level can be overridden. Same pattern throughout.
